Package: ppod
Type: Package
Title: Posterior Predictive Optimal Biological Dose Selection with
    Continuous Toxicity and Efficacy Endpoints
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Author", "One", email = "author.one@institution.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000")),
    person("Author", "Two", role = "aut"),
    person("Author", "Three", role = "aut"))
Description: A Bayesian phase I/II adaptive design for optimal biological
    dose (OBD) selection with continuous toxicity and efficacy endpoints.
    Dose assignment and final selection are based on posterior predictive
    expected utility evaluated under the joint toxicity-efficacy
    distribution on a bounded transformed scale. The package implements
    joint, marginal, and plug-in posterior predictive utility criteria;
    posterior predictive admissibility gates; a binary-endpoint BOIN12
    comparator (Lin et al. 2020); and the 12 simulation scenarios used
    in the accompanying manuscript. Posterior inference uses a Laplace
    approximation suitable for large operating-characteristics studies.
